    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJxq7WC0z8aS8IB38RhphxMcVSZewfN0TKoWH8uT=k-s256",
                "account_id": 23213362,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 17306533,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/17306533/abhinav-ojha",
                "reputation": 43,
                "display_name": "Abhinav Ojha"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1645108679,
            "creation_date": 1645108679,
            "body": "<p>Just create an object for the class Game.<\/p>\n<pre><code>new Game();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>Also the <code>frame.setLocation(null);<\/code> throws an error.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 71160159,
            "question_id": 71160005
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-YT3dBTDRsd0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAQs/lt4dWyKqaOg/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
                "account_id": 12596093,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 9160673,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/9160673/marios-koni",
                "reputation": 143,
                "display_name": "Marios Koni"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1645109059,
            "creation_date": 1645109059,
            "body": "<p>That's why it is not a good idea to copy paste code blindly. You have two classes. A Game class which I assume will handle the game logic and a Window function which will handle the GUI related. In your Game class, you have the main function, which is the function java will look for when you start the program. But it's empty. That's why your program terminates. You should define an instance of the Game class, which in turn will trigger the Game constructor and your window will be initiated and then call whatever method you need.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 71160247,
            "question_id": 71160005
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ghgiel-9WK6CnuAls8dSOJXl0lQPyvlLt7Hnix7=k-s256",
                "account_id": 21345642,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 15715740,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15715740/prime-balpreet",
                "reputation": 16,
                "display_name": "Prime Balpreet"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1645109842,
            "creation_date": 1645109842,
            "body": "<p>Add a <code>new Game();<\/code> in the main method.\nInstead of <code>frame.setLocation(null);<\/code> do `frame.setRelativeLocation(null);<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 71160434,
            "question_id": 71160005
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/df1f1e3d452db18ddac898fd4beb8579?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 24289131,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 18234469,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/18234469/adri2210",
                "reputation": 1,
                "display_name": "Adri2210"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1645110970,
            "creation_date": 1645110970,
            "body": "<p>It works now, thanks guys! The problem was not the setLocationRelativetoNull(null); but that I forgot to create an object of the game class in the main method. And the Title was not being used because I created the Jframe frame = new Jframe(); instead of Jframe frame = new Jframe(title);<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 71160734,
            "question_id": 71160005
        }
